#compdef liara
# =============================================================================
# liara — Liara Cloud's "command line interface for Liara" — an
#         oclif-based TypeScript-Node CLI for the Liara cloud
#         platform (liara.ir, Iranian PaaS provider) supporting
#         app deployment, database management, object storage,
#         mail service, networking, virtual machines, and DNS
#         zone management.
#         Distinguishing from heroku-cli, flyctl, render-cli,
#         and other cloud-CLI tools by:
#           - 13 TOPIC GROUPS via oclif command tree:
#               * account            — manage multi-account login
#               * app                — app lifecycle (create /
#                                      delete / list / logs /
#                                      restart / shell / start /
#                                      stop)
#               * bucket             — object storage buckets
#                                      (create / delete / list)
#               * db                 — managed databases (create
#                                      / list / remove / resize
#                                      / start / stop) + backup
#                                      (create / download / list)
#               * deploy             — deploy an app from local
#                                      directory or Docker image
#               * disk                — persistent disk
#                                      management
#               * env                — environment variables
#                                      (list / set / unset)
#               * init               — initialize liara.json
#                                      project config
#               * login              — authenticate
#               * mail               — managed email service
#                                      (create / delete / list /
#                                      send)
#               * network            — virtual networks (create
#                                      / list)
#               * plan               — list available plans
#               * vm                 — virtual machines (create /
#                                      delete / info / list /
#                                      restart / start / stop)
#               * zone               — DNS zones (check / create
#                                      / delete / get / list) +
#                                      record (create / get /
#                                      list / remove / update)
#           - MULTI-ACCOUNT SUPPORT via `liara account add` —
#             multiple Liara accounts persisted in
#             ~/.liara/liara.json with current-account marker;
#             `liara account use <name>` switches; --account
#             flag temporarily overrides for one command
#           - DEPLOYMENT WITH DOCKER + ARCHIVE — `liara deploy`
#             either tars + uploads local directory, or accepts
#             pre-built Docker image via --image flag; supports
#             Docker build-args (--build-arg, multiple) and
#             custom Dockerfile (--dockerfile)
#           - PLATFORM AUTO-DETECTION — `liara deploy` detects
#             platform (node / php / python / django / laravel /
#             flask / django / dotnet / static / docker / etc.)
#             from project structure unless --platform is
#             explicit
#           - BUILD LOCATION SELECTION — `--build-location iran`
#             or `--build-location germany` chooses Liara build
#             cluster
#           - LIARA.JSON PROJECT CONFIG — `liara init`
#             scaffolds a liara.json file with platform-specific
#             defaults; subsequent commands read this for app /
#             port / disks defaults
#           - INTERACTIVE PROMPTS via inquirer for missing
#             required values (app name selection from list,
#             port number, etc.)
#           - PROGRESS BAR for source tarball upload via
#             `progress` package
#           - WEBSOCKET BUILD LOG STREAMING via `ws` — streams
#             real-time Docker build output during `liara deploy`
#           - SHAMSI-DATE-CONVERTER + chrono-node — Persian
#             (Shamsi) calendar conversion for timestamp display
#             targeted at Iranian users
#           - got 13.0.0 FOR ALL HTTP — every Liara API call goes
#             through got with extended options pre-configured
#             with Bearer auth token, proxy support
#             (https-proxy-agent), and async-retry for transient
#             failures
#         Used by: Iranian developers deploying apps to
#         Liara.ir, multi-region cloud teams using Liara's
#         Germany region, and as a reference implementation of
#         got + oclif + inquirer + ora + got + ws + async-retry
#         composition in TypeScript-Node CLIs.
#
# Author:  Liara Cloud (liara.ir) — Tehran-based Platform-as-a-
#          Service provider founded 2017.  liara CLI by MHE
#          (mhemrg120@gmail.com) + Liara engineering team.
#          Active development through 2026; current version
#          9.4.7.  License: MIT.
# Source:  https://github.com/liara-cloud/cli
#          https://github.com/liara-cloud/cli/blob/master/package.json
#          https://github.com/liara-cloud/cli/blob/master/src/base.ts
#          https://github.com/liara-cloud/cli/blob/master/src/commands/deploy.ts
# CLI:     src/base.ts + src/commands/* — uses @oclif/core
#          (Heroku's CLI framework; documented across many Node
#          completions).  Headline library: **got**
#          (oclif is documented elsewhere; got is the new
#          variant being documented here, completing Axis 16
#          three-language symmetry across Rust / Go / TS-Node).
# Library: got (https://github.com/sindresorhus/got —
#          "Human-friendly and powerful HTTP request library
#           for Node.js" — Sindre Sorhus.  Distinct from
#           reqwest (R649, Rust Axis 16 opener) and
#           go-resty/resty (R650, Go Axis 16 expansion) by
#           being:
#              1. FETCH-LIKE PROMISE API — got's central pattern
#                 is a fetch-style top-level function returning
#                 a Promise:
#                   import got from 'got';
#                   const data = await got('https://api.example.com')
#                       .json<User>();
#                 With response-typing generics for TypeScript.
#              2. INSTANCES via got.extend — create pre-
#                 configured got instances with default headers /
#                 base URL / timeout / hooks:
#                   const api = got.extend({
#                     prefixUrl: 'https://api.example.com',
#                     headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${token}` },
#                     timeout: { request: 30000 },
#                     retry: { limit: 3 },
#                     hooks: {
#                       beforeRequest: [refreshAuthIfExpired],
#                       afterResponse: [logResponse]
#                     }
#                   });
#                   const u = await api.get('users/42').json<User>();
#                 Liara CLI uses got.extend in base.ts to create
#                 a pre-authenticated instance for all API calls.
#              3. EXPONENTIAL-BACKOFF RETRY built-in — default
#                 retry config retries on network errors + 408 +
#                 413 + 429 + 500 + 502 + 503 + 504 with
#                 exponential delay; configurable via retry:
#                 { limit, methods, statusCodes, errorCodes,
#                 calculateDelay }
#              4. HOOK SYSTEM with 5 lifecycle phases —
#                 init / beforeRequest / beforeRedirect /
#                 beforeRetry / beforeError / afterResponse.
#                 Each phase accepts array of async functions
#                 receiving options + response, enabling
#                 middleware composition.
#              5. STREAMING via got.stream — got returns a
#                 Node Readable stream for download progress
#                 + piping to fs:
#                   stream.pipeline(
#                     got.stream(url),
#                     fs.createWriteStream(dest)
#                   );
#                 Liara uses this for tarball uploads.
#              6. HTTP/2 + HTTP/1.1 — opt-in HTTP/2 via http2:
#                 true; otherwise HTTP/1.1.
#              7. PAGINATION HELPER — got.paginate.each + got.
#                 paginate.all for following pagination links
#                 (Link header, X-Next-Page header, etc.) and
#                 yielding aggregated results.
#              8. PURE NODE.JS (no browser support) — got 12+
#                 dropped browser polyfills; targets Node.js 16+
#                 exclusively.  Smaller bundle (compared to
#                 axios which supports both).
#              9. TYPESCRIPT-NATIVE — full .d.ts type
#                 declarations; response.body type inferred
#                 from .json<T>() generic.
#             10. SINDRE-SORHUS / SORHUS ECOSYSTEM PROVENANCE —
#                 Sindre Sorhus's most-used HTTP library, part
#                 of the same Sorhus-ecosystem that includes
#                 chalk + ora + figlet + conf + dotenv + log-
#                 symbols + ... 1100+ npm packages by Sindre.)
# License: MIT (got); MIT (liara)
# Status:  got — 14,909+ stars on sindresorhus/got, ~40M weekly
#          npm downloads (TOP-10 most-downloaded HTTP client
#          for Node.js); foundational dependency of:
#            * Vercel CLI
#            * Netlify CLI
#            * Cloudflare wrangler (some parts)
#            * Sentry CLI
#            * Heroku CLI plugins
#            * AWS Amplify CLI
#            * Bitwarden CLI
#            * Storybook CLI
#            * Snyk CLI
#            * liara (THIS)
#            * 100,000+ npm packages
#          liara — 116+ stars on liara-cloud/cli, ~30k weekly
#          npm downloads, official CLI for Liara cloud platform.
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# CROSS-LANGUAGE CLI LIBRARY TAXONOMY MILESTONE — TS-NODE CROSSES TO 70 +
