#
# Pattern: R649 Rust=70 (reqwest — Axis 16 OPENS) → R650 Go=70
# (resty — Axis 16 expands to 2) → R651 TS-Node=70 (got THIS —
# Axis 16 completes 1/1/1 three-language symmetry) → expected
# R652 95th language.  This is the 3rd of 3 leader bumps in
# the current segment.
#
# This completion EXPANDS Axis 16 (HTTP CLIENTS) to THREE documented
# variants — symmetrically distributed across Rust (reqwest R649),
# Go (resty R650), and TS-Node (got THIS R651).  Axis 16 becomes
# the EIGHTH AXIS to reach 1/1/1 three-language symmetry (joining
# Axes 7 / 11 / 12 / 15 + Axes 4/5 from earlier rounds).
#
#   Axis 16 (HTTP CLIENTS) variants:
#     - reqwest (seanmonstar/reqwest) — R649 (_rustormy) — Rust
#       ASYNC + BLOCKING dual; built on hyper; rustls/native-tls;
#       serde JSON; Sean McArthur / Hyperium ecosystem
#     - resty (go-resty/resty) — R650 (_intercept) — Go FLUENT
#       BUILDER; automatic JSON/XML; retry + middleware hooks;
#       Mathew Roy / go-resty ecosystem
#     - got (sindresorhus/got) — R651 (THIS) — TS-Node FETCH-
#       LIKE Promise API; got.extend instances; exponential-
#       backoff retry; 5-phase hook system; Sindre Sorhus /
#       Sorhus ecosystem
#
# Three Axis 16 variants address THREE COMPLEMENTARY design
# approaches to HTTP client APIs:
#   reqwest            = ASYNC+BLOCKING dual + builder pattern +
#                         serde JSON (Rust)
#   resty              = FLUENT chained methods + auto JSON/XML +
#                         retry + middleware (Go)
#   got                = PROMISE/fetch-like + got.extend instances
#                         + exponential retry + 5-phase hooks
#                         (TS-Node)
#
# Each language's Axis 16 library addresses a DIFFERENT design
# pain point:
#   - Rust reqwest: hyper too low-level; reqwest is friendly
#                    facade with async/blocking duality
#   - Go resty:     net/http requires verbose manual marshaling;
#                    resty provides fluent chained builders
#   - Node got:     fetch lacks retry + middleware + streams;
#                    got adds all three with TypeScript-native
#                    Promise API
